Explanation of how the parameter list was derived:

- Routing: hello.go mounts UserRegister at v1.Group("/user") where v1 is "/api". UserRegister maps PUT "/" to UserUpdate, so the endpoint is PUT /api/user.
- Authentication: UserUpdate executes after the AuthMiddleware(true) (see hello.go and middleware registration). The middleware extracts tokens from the Authorization header or an access_token query parameter (see users/middlewares.go: MyAuth2Extractor and AuthorizationHeaderExtractor). If no valid token is presented, the middleware aborts with 401. Therefore the endpoint accepts an Authorization header (required) and also supports access_token as an alternative (query).
- Request body: UserUpdate uses NewUserModelValidatorFillWith and then Bind(c) to bind and validate the incoming JSON into UserModelValidator.User structure. The validator defines the JSON payload as {"user": { "username": string, "email": string, "password": string, "bio": string, "image": string }} (see users/validators.go). Binding tags indicate required fields and constraints:
